data.title: Kansas State University
data.text:
Kansas State University students earn spring semester honors

Friday, June 9, 2023

Editor's note: If a county or state is not listed, there were no honor students from that area. If a Manhattan area address was given as a permanent address, the student will be listed in the permanent address county and also in the county for their high school on record. If a student's name is not listed, please contact the appropriate college dean’s office or the Office of the Registrar at 785-532-6254 or registrar@k-state.edu for assistance.

Written by: Taylor Provine, taylorhm@k-state.edu

MANHATTAN — Nearly 4,000 Kansas State University students have earned semester honors for their academic performance in the spring 2023 semester.

Students earning a grade point average for the semester of 3.75 or above on at least 12 graded credit hours receive semester honors along with commendations from their deans. The honors are also recorded on their permanent academic records.

The following students earned semester honors for the spring 2023 semester from Kansas State University:
